## Summary

**Problem**: Race condition in the `purchase` method. The stock check (`if self.stock >= amount`) and decrement (`self.stock -= amount`) were not atomic. Multiple concurrent users could all read the same stock value, pass the check, and then all decrement - resulting in negative stock.

**Fix**: Added an `asyncio.Lock` (`self._lock`) and wrapped the critical section with `async with self._lock:`. This ensures only one coroutine can execute the check-and-decrement sequence at a time, making the operation atomic.
